    "Diagnosing malaria or naming malaria as the user's condition",
    "Diagnosing typhoid or naming typhoid as the user's condition",
    "Prescribing antimalarial medicines or antibiotics",
    "Recommending dosage, dose changes, or how many tablets to take",
    "Saying fever is harmless or that no clinician review is needed when danger signs exist",
    "Interpreting Widal, malaria test, or typhoid panel results as proof of a disease",
    "Naming malaria, typhoid, or any specific illness as a conclusion",
    "Telling the user to start, stop, or change medicines bought at a chemist",
    "Replacing emergency services or a clinician visit when danger signs appear"
  ],
